# Feature: Application Mode / Web Page Mode Toggle

## Goal

Add a toggle in the header's "more" menu to switch between "Application Mode" (header + body full height, footer hidden) and "Web Page Mode" (normal layout). This enables professional, compact app presentation on all routes, responsive to user preference.

## Steps

1. Update layout to support both modes:
   - Application Mode: header and body fill viewport, footer hidden
   - Web Page Mode: normal layout
2. Add toggle to header's "more" menu
3. Implement state management for mode (context/global)
4. Ensure layout is fully responsive
5. Add tests for layout and toggle
6. Audit UI/UX and code quality
7. Update documentation and traceability

